BS original programming]]\n[[Category:1965 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1966 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:Television series by CBS Television Studios]]\n[[Category:American legal television series]]\n[[Category:American drama television series]]\n[[Category:Black-and-white American television programs]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Filmways]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = The Trials of O'Brien\n| image                = Trials of OBrien.JPG\n| caption              = Peter Falk and Joanna Barnes, 1965.\n| genre                = [[Legal drama]]/[[situation comedy|comedy]]\n| runtime              = 48 mins.\n| creator              = Gene Wang\n| developer            = Gene Wang\n| producer             = \n| executive_producer   = \n| starring             = [[Peter Falk]]<br />[[Elaine Stritch]]<br />[[Joanna Barnes]]\n| voices               = \n| narrated             = \n| theme_music_composer = Sid Ramin\n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| country              = USA\n| location             = \n| language             = English\n| camera               = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| company              = [[Filmways]]<br>Mayo Productions, The O'Brien Company\n| distributor          = CBS Enterprises (1965\u201371)<br>[[Viacom (original)|Viacom]] (1971\u201395)<br>[[Paramount Domestic Television]] (1995\u20132006)<br>[[CBS Paramount Domestic Television]] (2006\u201307)<br>[[CBS Television Distribution]] (2007\u2013present)\n| network              = [[CBS]]\n| picture_format       = [[Black-and-white]] \n| audio_format         = [[Monaural]] \n| first_aired          = {{start date|1965|09|18}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|1966|05|27}}\n| num_seasons           = 1\n| num_episodes         = 22\n| list_episodes        = \n}}\n\n'''''The Trials of O'Brien''''' is a 1965 [[television program|television series]] starring [[Peter Falk]] as a sordid [[Shakespeare]]-quoting [[lawyer]] and featuring [[Elaine Stritch]] as his [[secretary]] and [[Joanna Barnes]] as his ex-wife.\n\nThe series ran for only 22 episodes on [[CBS|CBS Television]] between September 18, 1965 and March 18, 1966.\n\nAmong its guest stars: [[Milton Berle]], [[Robert Blake (actor)|Robert Blake]], [[David Carradine]], [[Faye Dunaway]], [[Britt Ekland]], [[Tammy Grimes]], [[Buddy Hackett]], [[Gene Hackman]], [[Frank Langella]], [[Angela Lansbury]], [[Cloris Leachman]], [[Roger Moore]], [[Rita Moreno]], [[Estelle Parsons]], [[Joanna Pettet]], [[Brock Peters]], [[Tony Roberts (actor)|Tony Roberts]], and [[Martin Sheen]].\n\nFalk often said that he actually liked this financially unsuccessful series much better than his later smash-hit ''[[Columbo (TV series)|Columbo]]''.{{Citation needed|date=February 2007}}\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#500050; width:20px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#500050\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#500050; width:135px\"| Directed by:\n! style=\"background:#500050; width:155px\"| Written by:\n! style=\"background:#500050; width:135px\"| Air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 1\n| Title = Over Defence Is Out\n| DirectedBy = [[Stuart Rosenberg]]\n| WrittenBy = Richard Alan Simmons\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1965|9|18}}\n| ShortSummary = O'Brien represents a client who was charged with murder after being released from prison. Guest star: [[Vincent Gardenia]]\n| LineColor = 500050\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 2\n| Title = Bargain Day on the Street of Regret\n| DirectedBy = [[Bernard L. Kowalski]]\n| WrittenBy = Irving Gaynor Neiman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1965|9|25}}\n| ShortSummary = After winning a boxer in a dice game, O'Brien must defend him when he is charged in a fatal stabbing. Guest stars: [[Herschel Bernardi]] and [[Robert Blake (actor)|Robert Blake]].\n| LineCol